What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course to any serious musician wishing to continue performance study. Obviously, a significant amount of outside practice is necessary, but you definitely get out what you put in. My instructor was very skilled and working with her has been a fantastic experience; I feel we have gotten to know each other well on both a musical and personal level.
I would recommend this class. It is nice to get credit for taking lessons.

I would highly recommend this course to any violinist who wants the best instruction from the best teachers and professors. My professor was able to fix all of the problems I was struggling to fix for years in less than a month, and she is incredibly encouraging and friendly.
